                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3731/908: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-08-15T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 15, 1934—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>143. Your 393 and 394, August 15. You are authorized to insert at beginning of
                    new Article VI the phrase “on and after July 1, 1935.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
